reviewText: Love the movies and they arrived ahead of schedule
Love everything John Wayne ever made He's the best
I love John Wayne this was the perfect box set.
A rare film that takes place during the Vietnam war.  Well done.

In these "perilous" days, the Duke reminds us why we HAVE armed forces.  The drawback/feature of the packaging is that all three discs are stacked on a single spindle.  Now, if only they could have found a way to connect "McClintock" to these three features, I wouldn't need another John Wayne collection (Just kidding). Luckily you don't need to wade through all those "coming soon to DVD" prequels with this collection.
What a great combination for his movies. In Harm's Way is by far my favorite John Wayne military movie. Can't wait to buy other John Wayne combos.
Awesome fast shipping. Highly recommended !!!!  Product exactly as advertised. It's always a surprise receiving product AHEAD of estimated receipt date.
I love the Green Berets.  The Flying Leathernecks was a little too much for me to watch.

Three Movies Featuring The Great John Wayne: 'The Green Berets',

 'Flying Leathernecks', The Story Of General Claire Chennault's Flying Tigers, The American Volunteer Group, And About 100 Curtiss P-40 Warhawk Fighters, With Shark Tooth Designs Painted On Them--To Take Advantage Of The Japanese Soldiers' Phobia Of Sharks--Flew For China, Against Japan.

And Otto Preminger's Rip-Snortin' Stories Of America's Entry Into World War II, 'In Harm's Way', One Of The All Time Classics. This Is A Pretty Good Selection Of Three Great Movies.
John Wayne exhibited what a true Special Forces really meant!
